# CrediQuest Development Rules

## TypeScript
- Use explicit types over 'any'
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Use const assertions for literal types

## Solidity
- All state-changing functions need ReentrancyGuard
- Use OpenZeppelin contracts as base
- Follow CEI pattern (Checks-Effects-Interactions)
- No floating pragmas - use solidity ^0.8.20
- Prefer inline assembly only for gas optimization (document why)
- Use state machine pattern for lifecycle management
- Emit events for all state changes
- Test with multi-member scenarios (12+ members)

## Frontend
- All UI components must work without wallet connection (read-only mode)
- Game canvas must handle resize events
- Use Zustand for state management
- Mobile-first responsive design

## Testing
- Foundry for contract testing
- Hardhat for deployment
- Fuzz tests for financial logic
